docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:841:Measure how long it takes to unload one model and load another (relevant if models must be rotated due to memory constraints).
docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:851:| Same-socket concurrency degradation | < 40% | Two models on one socket |
docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:853:| Model swap latency (fast models) | < 15 seconds | Cold load from disk to RAM |
docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:854:| Model swap latency (heavy models) | < 45 seconds | 65-87 GB load |
docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:952:| G3 | RSS <= 100 GB (fast models) or <= 400 GB (heavy models) | Phase 1 |
docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:953:| G4 | Sanity check correctness (GDN/Mamba models) | Phase 1 |
docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:966:| S4 | Model swap latency (when needed) < 30 seconds for fast models |
